    "16560464437d7fe44b": {
      "type": "loop-article-richtext",
      "blocks": {
        "1656046443b1b2d9f5-0": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When it comes to actually giving that feedback to others, we tend to get a bit nervous. We love giving kudos, high fives and celebrating wins, but sharing critical feedback can feel a lot harder. Potentially, you’re putting your professional relationships at risk.<\/p><p>So how do you break through the anxiety?<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "1656046443b1b2d9f5-0"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "desktop_content_position": "center",
        "content_alignment": "center",
        "color_scheme": "#ffffff",
        "full_width": true,
        "padding_top": 40,
        "padding_bottom": 52
      }
    },
    "16604607234acd9044": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "166046072211f39075-0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Tips on Giving Tips",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "166046072211f39075-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>What’s the most useful piece of feedback you’ve ever received?<\/p><p>Chances are, it was something constructive. Something that might have felt awkward or uncomfortable at first. But which helped you grow as a professional and as a person.<\/p><p>Outside input is one of the best ways to improve. It helps us learn from others, move on from mistakes, and become better at what we do.<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "d6a51c5b-3b59-4ae3-b3d3-43f0ad37ee2e": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "A Feedback-rich culture",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "fd098bcc-1457-415e-bcbc-9eb51f262215": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Loop’s People Manager, Bas Moeyaert, shared some of his top tips for building the systems and strategies that are needed. As <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/sites\/gradsoflife\/2022\/06\/30\/3-ways-to-tackle-hirings-mammoth-bias-problem\/?\">Forbes<\/a> put it, “creating a feedback-rich culture leans on the foundation of trust, healthy communication and safety.”<\/p><p><\/p><p>These approaches help us to reinforce clear, open communication that makes it easier to share constructive feedback, as well as praise. Because at Loop, a healthy and supportive working environment is non-negotiable.<\/p>"
          }
        },
        "4bddc5cf-f6dc-420b-8158-3c41639b641b": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "#1: Building processes",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "05e7bc80-2a3c-419d-a3cd-8e5269dd8c84": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Every week, each Looper fills in a 15-minute online survey. It includes a quick update on how their week went and what they enjoyed, as well as the things they’re struggling with and how their manager can help with that.<\/p><p>The results give our team managers a real insight into what’s going well and what’s not so effective – from the point of view of all of their employees.<\/p><p>The survey has quickly become a habit. It’s quick, it’s easy, and it gives people a safe space – in which they can raise an issue that they might not feel able to raise in another context.<\/p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "166046072211f39075-0",
        "166046072211f39075-1",
        "d6a51c5b-3b59-4ae3-b3d3-43f0ad37ee2e",
